'''Peter Wilhelm Kreydahl Bøckman Jr.''' (14 May 1927 &ndash; 17 December 2006) was a [[Norway|Norwegian]] [[religious studies]] scholar.

He was born in [[Skjervøy]] municipality in [[Troms county]], Norway.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia |year=2007 |title=Bøckman, Peter Wilhelm Kreydahl |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location= |url=https://snl.no/Peter_Wilhelm_Kreydahl_B%C3%B8ckman%2Fnorsk_professor}}</ref> He was a grandson of bishop [[Peter W. K. Bøckman, Sr.]] and brother of journalist Knut Bøckman.<ref>{{cite encyclopedia |year=2007 |title=Bøckman |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location= |url=https://snl.no/B%C3%B8ckman/norsk_slekt}}</ref> He graduated as [[cand.theol.]] in 1953, and following studied in the [[United States]] and [[Sweden]], he was hired as a lecturer at the [[University of Oslo]] in 1967. From 1975 to 1997 he was a professor of [[religious studies]] at the [[University of Trondheim]]. He published several books on theological topics.

